description:
Dark Productions started publishing print and web comics in 2012. Our goal is to tell stories that have value and express creativity through a unique artistic voice. Our inspiration comes from life experiences as well as strange dreams. Which ever the case may be, the words and images seem to flow better during the night.

This small press company is run by comic book artist and writer, Nguyen Dong and his wife, Leen Isabel.
name: Dark Productions

description:
This publisher is based in Texas and prides itself on having an honest and personal relationship with it's authors and pay them traditional royalties.

Black Rose Writing was founded in 2006 and it features a wide array of genres. The company prints the books on-demand in an endless print run. It's main channels for sale are the bigger book selling companies like Amazon, Ingram, Baker & Taylor and Barnes & Noble.

Black Rose Writing is open for submissions.
name: Black Rose Writing

This is an imprint of Harper Collins Publishers and started in 1981.

Long considered the leader in film and television publishing, Newmarket Press was brought under the It Books imprint and continues to publish entertainment-related titles. The Book of Mormon by Trey Parker and Matt Stone; Testimony: The Legacy of Schindler's List and the Shoah Foundation by Steven Spielberg as well as screenplays by Judd Apatow, Marc Boal, Diablo Coady, Charlie Kaufman, and Seth Rogen.
